                            <comment id="491907" author="JIRAUSER19283" created="Fri, 27 Mar 2026 01:36:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Computing parities and recovering a lost stripe is the same code and performs the same : ec_encode_data().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Running tests on the plain C version we currently use, the throughput for computing the parities for --ec 5+2&lt;br/&gt;
fluctuates between ~350MB/sec/core to ~450MB/sec/core.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tests done on a KVM VM on a dell laptop.&lt;br/&gt;
The throughput number is measured as such:&lt;br/&gt;
Number of input stripes : 5 * stripe size : 1MB.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Testing throughput for EC computations on the upstream hand-optimized assembler versions clocks in at&lt;br/&gt;
~35GB/sec/core to ~40GB/sec/core&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1, 40GB/sec/core should be plenty fast&lt;br/&gt;
2, we should switch to the assembler version of the library.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Note, these numbers are only for the EC computations.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
